				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Writer behind Fantastic Four reboot now writing Netflix's Death Note series...
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1850986">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I enjoyed it overall.  I was a bit surprised by it though.  When I saw the premise and got into the first episode I figured it would be a slow decline as he started using the power and it would then engulf him.  Instead he picked up the notebook and went all megalomaniac immediately.  After that the only kindof meh moments I had were the usual failing of all &quot;super smart&quot; characters in shows where they make the crazy leap to the truth effortlessly at times.  The teen romance bits also annoyed me a little, but they do in almost every medium these days.  Overall I liked it.  <br />
<br />
I also enjoyed the two live movies from Japan.  The dubbing was by the anime voice actors and the computer generation matched the anime.  It wasn't as deep as the anime, but there is only so much you can do in a movie setting.<br />
<br />
I always wondered why they hadn't Americanized it in some form already for release here.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
