		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Writer behind Fantastic Four reboot now writing Netflix's Death Note series...
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1850998">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Ackar</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1850996#post1850996" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">You do know they are filming the GitS live action currently right?<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/celebrities/78505688/scarlett-johanssons-ghost-in-the-shell-movie-to-start-filming-in-central-wellington.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Scarlett Johansson's Ghost in the Shell movie to start filming in central Wellington</a><br />
<br />
Guess which character Scarlett's playing...  <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Roll Eyes (Sarcastic)" class="inlineimg" /></div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yeah and it is going to be complete shit. Motoko is the best. It's also going to be difficult to pull off GitS's aesthetics and tech in a believable way. They can, but they are going to have to dump a lot of money into CGI to pull it off. The entire location will have to be CGI as well. After Motoko finding someone who can play the chief well will be difficult. He's subtle in a lot of ways. Some of the surrounding cast in Section 9 is one dimensional though.<br />
<br />
I don't know how they will be able to do the scenes were the characters go into autistic mode in a compelling way either. I don't see them using a lot of scenes where everyone is talking to one another but being visibly silent which happens quite a bit in GitS.<br />
<br />
There is no way they don't change the main antagonist drastically either in the US. They won't retain the same ending either. It's too introspective and won't gel with the POV studios have that everything should leave the audience happy. GitS isn't an upbeat universe and has a lot of philosophical influences that formed the world and story. And philosophy is the only domain more hated than mathematics in the US.<br />
<br />
IMO all of the films are a lot better than any of the manga though. The only part of the manga I liked are the kajillion footnotes the author put in it.<br />
<br />
They won't capture Batou or Toguso well either, either cutting them out entirely or making them irrelevant. The US doesn't have a culture where cybernetics and robotics is in the public consciousness aside from novelty or as some villain. The conversations around AI are completely fucked as well and ignorant. There is not any social awareness surround dystopic societies either.<br />
<br />
And all of those things are prerequisites for a film like GitS to ever have any success or exist in the first place.<br />
<br />
I don't think making GitS live action makes sense in the first place though. A story in the same universe could be great but what makes making GitS live action difficult is that Motoko switches bodies so frequently that either there are a ton of actresses or the actress is CGI'd a lot and is relegated to doing voice overs.<br />
<br />
They could adapt GitS's universe to a US setting though and make some story set in that, but trying to turn GitS's universe into something for a US audience isn't something that is achievable when the US has never made a main stream film about any of its topics successfully even though the US has had a lot of great science fiction authors and Phillip K. Dick owns dystopia.<br />
<br />
Along with PKD, William Gibson who launched cyberpunk as we know it was born here. If we want to be super technical though there are at least two dystopia films that were good: &quot;A Scanner Darkly&quot; and &quot;Blade Runner: Final Cut.&quot;<br />
<br />
The only time we have ever seen Scar Jo act well was when she was only doing voice over in &quot;Her&quot; and her dead face wasn't on screen shattering believability. Despite being entirely a cyborg Motoko is very expressive in comparison and contemplative, moving through a range of emotions over the course of every film. Scar Jo cannot pull that off at all.<br />
<br />
While Motoko's a bombshell for most of GitS there is no reason they have to cast one because her shell is unimportant other than being female in appearance (Motoko always chooses to appear as a female, something that is delved into in one of the films or series). Eva Green would rock this role because she can pull off any emotion believably no matter how crazy as fuck it is.<br />
<br />
Charlize Theron would have been a much better choice if they want to choose someone who matches Motoko's appearance more though. She already was good in Aeon Flux playing a very similar role and basically carried the film. And Theron's an actually amazing actress able to move between the huge range of emotions that Motoko requires.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
