<br />
They changed words so it fits the mouth flaps better of course but the actual meaning of what was being said would be different and the way it was expressed would have different emotions behind them to the point that it would change what was happening in the scene. <br />
<br />
I think that is strange because English generally works better for music which is always more emotional than anything else. I haven't ever liked any Asian languages with music though which I wouldn't expect. I like Spanish a lot for music, maybe somewhat more than English.
